{ In situations like these, where Black doesn't do much to fight for the center, we can } { (and should) } { become stingy and take more space in the center. } 
1.c4 $1 {[%csl Gc4]} {[%csl Gd4]} {[%csl Ge4]} { Before developing the knight on [c3], we can take even more space in the center. Whenever it will be challenged and only then! by …e5 or …c5, we can push …d4-[d5], restricting the bishop on [b7]. } ( {(✅ alternative)} 1.f4! { is also perfectly playable here, as White's center isn't in any danger. } )  *

