{ Here, Black gained some central space with ...[d7]-[d5]. However, White can now strike with another central push. Considering the risks involved, should they go for it? } 
1.e4 $1 {[%cal Gf1d3]} {[%csl Gc4]} {[%csl Gd4]} {[%csl Rd5]} {[%csl Ge4]} {[%csl Gf1]} { They should, absolutely. } { That is why the best for Black was to play …Nf6 instead of …Nd7, preventing this move. White now opens up lines for their pieces and takes out the only central pawn Black has d5. }  *

