{ What are the pros and cons of taking space in the center with White here? } 
1.d4 $1 { The pros of opening up lines for their pieces are more important in comparison to the fact that White actually exchanges a central pawn for a relatively lateral pawn c5. It would be worse if White simply played a move like [d2]-[d3], leaving Black with more central control the [c5]-pawn is still fighting for the center, but having less space for their pieces. } cxd4  { Otherwise, White would advance the pawn further, gaining too much space in the center. } 
2.Nxd4  {[%cal Gc1e3]} {[%cal Gd1e2]} { Now the queen will eventually come to [e2], and the [a1]-rook will go on [d1], putting pressure on the [d6]-pawn. }  *

