{ Should White take space in the center, or would it be too compromising since they would have to sustain it? } 
1.e4 $1 { White will indeed have to sustain the center, but they will do so by developing their pieces on natural squares like Nc3. } Nf6  
2.Nc3  { Now neither …Bb4, nor …c5 shouldn't bother White, who can enjoy their space advantage. } Bb4  ( { ✓ } 2...c5 3.d5 {(. In this case not always, the [d5]-pawn will be a tough pawn to handle.)} ) 
3.Bd3  {[%cal Gd3e4]} {[%cal Ge1g1]} {[%csl Be4]} { Protecting the [e4]-pawn. And White keeps developing. } ( 3. Bd3 3...Bxc3 { is not a threat in this position. } )  *

