1.e4 $5 ( 1. e4 { This is an ambitious move. The main idea is that after } 1...Bb7 2.Bd3 { , we keep developing our pieces, and it is yet again hard for Black to challenge White's center. } ) ( { ✅ } 1.Nf3 { is a healthy alternative. After } 1...Bb7 { , White can develop slowly with moves like [e3]-[Bd3], although they will need much more time pushing [e4] in the future. } ) c5 $1 { Apparently, here, this is the best response for Black. } ( { ✓ } 1...Bb7 2.Bd3 Bxc3+ 3.bxc3 { , and White has a powerful center and the double pawns don't matter here. } ) 
