[Event "Healthy Opening Habits for Middlegame Success"]
[White "1b) Develop Your Pieces Efficiently"]
[Black "1b) Develop Your Pieces Efficiently"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1"]

{ Developing your pieces is a basic principle in chess. It quickly becomes obvious that you cannot build any serious threats with only one or two pieces, so you should develop most of your pieces before entering the battle. Therefore, being able to do so efficiently is vital: 🔹be careful about developing your pieces where they can't stay safe: they could be kicked, and therefore, you will lose time, which is something you should definitely avoid in the initial stage of the game not only there; 🔹be aware of the possible pawn advances in the center from your opponent: your development moves should fight for the center; 🔹think about concrete consequences of your development moves: make sure you don't have any concrete problems; 🔹in closed positions: priorities change, and so do natural squares for your pieces. } 
