[FEN "r1bqkb1r/pppp1p1p/2n2np1/4p3/2B1P3/5Q2/PPPP1PPP/RNB1K1NR w KQkq - 0 1"]

{ After going for Scholar's Mate, White spent some time being disappointed when Black managed to defend against it. Now it's time to play serious chess. } 
1.Ne2 $1 { Although late, White is just slightly worse here. It's not too late to start doing things appropriately. } ( { ❌ } 1.Qb3?? { is too much! Development is key, and this is searching for trouble. } 1...Nd4! { Such irresponsible opening play from White should be punished. Black is basically winning already. } {(( 1...Qe7 is also possible.))} 2.Qd3 {(( 2.Bxf7+ would accelerate defeat after. 2...Ke7 3.Qc4 b5 -+ and the [f7]-bishop is lost.))} 2...d5! { Black keeps developing their pieces quickly. } 3.Bxd5 {(( 3.exd5 Bf5 is the same. ))} 3...Nxd5 4.exd5 Bf5 { , and Black wins. } ) Bg7  
2.O-O  { Time for king safety. } O-O  
3.Nbc3  { The best approach: keep developing while protecting [d5] and the [e4]-pawn. } d6  
4.d3  {[%csl Rf3]} { And the game goes on, even if Black is slightly better. }  *

