{ White has a good position here and can steer the game in several satisfying directions. But what is the best move in terms of taking space? } 
1.f4 $1 ( { ✓ } 1.Nf3 { also works, but once again, if we can take space, we should do it. Eventually, you will also understand what to do with this space. At the beginning, in my opinion, it's important to understand the concept of ‘critical moves’. } ) e5  
2.Nf3  {[%csl Gd4]} {[%csl Ge4]} {[%csl Gf4]} { White has more space in the center. }  *

