{ The following position was a tabiya in the late 2010s, arising from the Semi-Tarrasch. How should Black proceed? } Bb4+ $1 { Developing with tempo and exchanging an extra piece, having less space. Black prioritizes castling, postponing their queenside development, where Black remains flexible. } ( { ✕ } 1...Be7?! 2.Bc4 O-O 3.O-O { with an extra minor piece on the board, Black has less space to develop their other pieces. To illustrate it, you can see that the [e7]-square is not available for Black's queen. } ) ( { ✕ } 1...Nc6?! { . Often the knight is developed on [d7], not having to deal with the potential [d4]-[d5] push with tempo. } 2.Be2 Bb4+ 3.Bd2 Bxd2+ 4.Qxd2 O-O 5.O-O { . } ) 
2.Bd2  Bxd2+  
3.Qxd2  O-O  {[%cal Gb8d7]} {[%cal Gb7b6]} {[%cal Gc8b7]} { Now that Black has castled, the decision of where to develop the queenside pieces is handled. }  *

