{ A bishop fenced behind its own pawns is often called a 'bad' bishop because it can’t control many squares and lacks activity. Such bishops generally don’t have a bright future. That's why it's common practice to exchange them early, even before developing other pieces. This method is particularly effective in closed positions, where we can invest a few tempi without risking being dangerously underdeveloped } 
1.--   *

