{ Often, our problems in a position stem from a single enemy piece causing trouble. While this may seem logical, many players overlook the importance of exchanging their opponent’s dangerous pieces. We previously discussed the value of exchanging a strong enemy bishop. Here, we extend that concept to any piece, including pawns. Exchanging a strong enemy pawn is a valuable idea, which we will explore further when we deal with pawn play. The two steps to exchanging the opponent’s best piece are: 1 Identify the strongest piece. This is not always as straightforward as it seems: the most valuable piece is not always the strongest one. 2 Assess whether it’s possible to exchange this piece while maintaining attention to other aspects of the position. Let’s explore some standard situations where this concept is applied. } 
1.--   *

