{ Our knights are eager to occupy outposts whenever possible. However, they are often vulnerable to being exchanged by enemy pieces, particularly knights. That's why it's logical to eliminate these opposing knights, ideally trading them for our bishops, who are less likely to occupy those outposts themselves. This is a common practice we should remember when fighting for outposts. } 
1.--   *

