{ A common beginner mistake is to release central pawn tension as soon as the opportunity arises. Developing the ability to maintain our options and delay captures when possible is a vital skill for improvement. This particular exchange, known as Rubinstein’s Exchange – first implemented by the legendary Polish Grandmaster Akiba Rubinstein – has a clear purpose and appears in various openings, as the [c4]-[d5] tension is quite common. } 
1.--   *

