{ How to play sound chess in this position? } 
1.Be3  { A healthy developing move, not caring about the two expanding moves b5 and [g5], as they are not a threat. } ( { ✅ } 1.a4 { is good as an expansion of White on the queenside itself, but not as prophylaxis against the [b7]-[b5] push. } ) ( { ✕ } 1.h4?! { is unnecessary here, as [g7]-[g5] isn't a healthy expansion from Black. That's why White shouldn't worry about it and improve elsewhere instead. } ) b5 $6 { Now is a mistake. } 
2.a4 $1 {[%cal Ga4b5]} {[%csl Ba4]} { Black has to choose between spoiling the structure and spoiling the structure without compensation. } ( 2. a4 { What I mean is that after } 2...bxa4 {((✕ 2...a6?! can't be played, because of 3.axb5 and 3...axb5?? is not possible because of the hanging [a8]-rook.))} {((✕ 2...b4?! would lead to White’s advantage after 3.cxb4 Bxb4 4.Rc1 , with pressure on the backward [c6]-pawn.))} 3.Rxa4 { , Black now has a weak a-pawn. } )  *

