{ What is Black's idea, and how should White prevent it? } 
1.Re1 $3 { Once again, in this kind of position where White has more space, it is much more important to prevent our counterpart from playing active moves rather than becoming active ourselves, as we already have space advantage as our asset, especially with all the pieces on the board. White prevents ...[d6]-[d5], one of the main ideas for Black. } ( { ✕ } 1.f4?! { runs into another pawn break: } 1...e5! { and Black will open up lines for their pieces. } ) d5 $6 { This move is terrible. Better is to just play a waiting move, such as ...[g6] or ...[h6]. } 
2.e5 $1 { And Black would have no good squares for the knight. }  *

