{ How many times have you witnessed a back-rank mate? Growing up as a chess player, I often found myself cringing at such moments, and unfortunately, I fell victim to it a few times. In 2023, during a rapid tournament against an Armenian GM, I was deciding how to protect my extra pawn in a rook endgame. After opting to protect it from the side, I was stunned to be checkmated on the back rank. My opponent couldn’t believe his eyes, and neither could I. I covered my face in disbelief, and the weight of the mistake hit me hard. In this chapter, we’ll learn how to avoid this painful fate and create 'Luft' a German term for “air” – a flight square for the king. } 
1.--   *

