{ This is a typical position from a Rossolimo [Bxc6] - ...[dxc6] opening, played for example in the Caruana – Carlsen match from London 2018. } Nd7 $5 {[%cal Gd7f8]} {[%cal Gf8e6]} {[%cal Ge6d4]} {[%csl Bd4]} { Black proceeds with this typical maneuver. Being the position quite closed, Black can postpone castling. Even if [d4] is not an outpost, it's going to be uncomfortable for White to kick this knight with [c3], as the [d3]-pawn would become weak. } ( { In case of ✅ } 1...O-O 2.Nc3 Ne8! {(( 2...Nd7 3.Be3 and the [f8]-square is not available.))} 3.Be3 { Black would have to lose a tempo for [b7]-[b6] here. } ) 
2.Nc3  Nf8  
3.Be3  Ne6  {[%cal Ge6d4]} {[%csl Gc5]} {[%cal Ge6c5]} { And Black is right on time. }  *

