{ In a Réti kind of position, where White hasn't committed to [d2]-[d4] but has a pawn on [d3], the [a4] idea is typical, provoking ...[b5]-[b4]. } 
1.Nb1 $1 {[%cal Gb1d2]} {[%cal Gd2c4]} { Even if it looks like a passive move, this is the best way to improve your knight by investing a few tempi. } ( { ❌ } 1.Ne4?! { would allow Black to improve their position dramatically after } 1...Nxe4 2.dxe4 c4! { , already creating a passed pawn on the queenside. } ) ( { ❌ } 1.Nb5? { is an impulsive aggressive move, which will backfire heavily after } 1...Qb8 { and the [b7]-knight is in danger. } ) ( { ✕ } 1.Na2 { is the wrong direction, as now the knight literally has no future. } )  *

