1.Nd2  {[%cal Gd2c4]} { Again, regrouping the knight immediately looks like the most important thing. } ( { ✓ } 1.O-O Nf6 { and yet again the [f3]-knight will take some time to reach [d5], as the [d2]-[f1]-[e3]-[d5] route is obstructed by the [f1]-rook. } ) ( { ✕ } 1.Nd5?! { is premature and quite a mistake, as the knight creates no threats and can be immediately challenged with } 1...Nf6 { . Black will keep developing, and White's remaining pieces will be poorly placed. } )  *

