{ As you may have noticed, bishops hold a special place in this course. Over the past few decades, starting with Fischer’s era, their value has been increasingly recognized, and we now have a deeper understanding of their strengths and optimal placement in battle. Choosing the most effective diagonal for a bishop is not always straightforward. As we will explore further in other chapters, bishops don’t always need to attack targets directly – they can also play a crucial supporting role from behind, controlling key squares. In this chapter, we will see how bishops can take on more constructive roles once their job on a particular diagonal is done } 
