{ A Maróczy English setup for White that has gone wrong for Black. There are many ways to proceed here, as Black lacks counterplay. How would you prepare the thematic [Nd5] jump with White? } 
1.h4 $1 {[%cal Gg2h3]} {[%cal Gc3d5]} {[%cal Gh3c8]} { In preparation of the [Nd5]-[Nxd5]-[cxd5] structure change, White prepares to improve their light-squared bishop, controlling several squares, including the crucial [c8]-square. The fact the [d6]-pawn is weak, and Black has less space will not allow Black to challenge this strong bishop from [h3] with a hypothetical [Be8]-[d7]. }  *

