{ A typical position in the modern Queen's Gambit Declined Carlsbad approach, which we will discuss in the course on several occasions. White's long-term playing is [e3]-[e4]. How to prepare it? Try to envision 2-3 preparatory moves. } 
1.f3 $1 {[%cal Gh4f2]} {[%cal Gf3e4]} {[%cal Rf6e4]} {[%cal Rf6g4]} {[%cal Rc8g4]} { A multi-purpose move. White's idea is to push their central pawns and to do so; they should prepare it. The [f2]-[f3] is quite a regular idea in this structure, as the bishop from [f2] will support the [d4]-pawn, preparing [e3]-[e4]. Furthermore, the move [f3] takes away the [e4]- and [g4]-squares from Black’s light pieces. } Be6  
