{ A French structure position, where Black decided to close the center with ...[c5]-[c4], which usually is quite dangerous. } Nb6 $1 {[%cal Ge8d7]} { This idea was a favorite of the great Viktor Korchnoi. } ( { ✕ } 1...O-O-O ?! { would be too dangerous, as now after } 2.b3 { Black's king would be in danger after the c- and b-files would open up. } ) 
2.Ng5  Bxg5  
3.Qxg5  Qd8  {[%cal Ge8d7]} { Black is probably slightly worse, but with their king on the queenside, they will have chances. }  *

