( { This kind of position became fashionable recently, as it derives from } 1.d4 Nf6 2.c4 g6 3.h4!? { variations, where Black reaches a Benoni structure, but allows White's pawn to reach [h6]. } ) 
1.Kf1 $1 {[%cal Ge2d3]} { The king steps aside. Here it's possible to sacrifice the exchange on [a1], as the dark squares would immediately become vulnerable. Castling short would be too slow, therefore this move becomes the most energetic option. }  *

