{ After the initial moves 1.c4 g6 2.d4 Bg7 3.e4 d6 4.Nc3 c5 5.d5 Bxc3!? 6.bxc3 , White has pushed the pawn until [h5]. What should Black do with their king? } Kd7 $1 {[%cal Gd7c7]} ( { ✅ } 1...Kd8 { is also possible, but } {1...Kd7 looks more like a mouse slip, and it can trigger your opponents! The king will be safe on [c7], and the other pieces will be able to develop and create counterplay on the kingside. } )  *

