{ In the Caro-Kann: Advanced Variation with 4.h4 , White can develop their knight to [e2]. The main idea for White here is worth knowing. } 
1.Ng3 $1 {[%csl Rf5]} { White is challenging the [f5]-knight. } Nxg3  ( { ✕ } 1...g6 { would stop the f-file from opening, but it would weaken a lot the dark squares, such as [f6]. } ) 
2.fxg3  {[%cal Gf1f7]} {[%cal Gf3g5]} {[%csl Yf7]} { Suddenly, the [f1]-rook is developed and White has potential threats along the f-file. }  *

