{ Once again, a seemingly innocent position after Black played ...[Bg4] and ...[Bxf3]. White should finish developing. Is it so simple, though? } 
1.Qd1 $1 {[%cal Ge1e2]} {[%cal Rd7e5]} {[%cal Re5f3]} { A patient move, preparing development. } ( { The rushing development move ✕ } 1.Be2?! { would be careless, as after } 1...Ne5 { , White's Queen would have no good squares to move and only one save one, } 2.Qh3 { . } ) ( { ✓ } 1.d4 { would used a tempo for the wrong thing, as White is rushing to castle. } 1...Qe7 { , and White is under pressure, as Black wants to follow up with ...[e7]-[e5] and to counter [cxd5] with ...[e5]-[e4]! } )  *

