{ This is a modern idea against the Catalan connected to an early ...[a7]-[a5]. How does the Queen on [c2] feel after the last Black's move ...[Nc6]? } 
1.a3 $1 {[%cal Yc6b4]} {[%csl Gc2]} { A must know move, securing the Queen on [c2], defending against possible ...[Nb4]. Even if it may not seem like ...[Nb4] is a big threat now, [a2]-[a3] is a necessary prophylaxis, so we should invest a tempo later or sooner better sooner for this move. Once we solve this issue, we can put the focus back on our development. }  *

