1.Qd2 $5 {[%cal Gd2f4]} {[%cal Gf4g4]} {[%cal Re7f6]} {[%csl Gd4]} {[%csl Ge5]} {[%csl Gg4]} {[%csl Rg7]} { Whenever there is a pawn on [e5], we would like our queen to be on [g4], because it would be the most aggressive square for the queen. The Queen would be targeting [g7], and there would be little to no ways for Black to kick it from there. Although with this awkward-looking move, White takes three ! tempi to reach [g4], it is worth it. } ( { ✅ } 1.Be3 { is perfectly playable, too. } )  *

