{ This concept is one of the easiest to grasp. Throughout this course, I aim to instill the habit of keeping the tension – not exchanging at the first opportunity. When we control when to open a file, we shouldn’t rush. Instead, we should wait for the most favorable conditions before committing. } 
1.--   *

[Event "Healthy Opening Habits for Middlegame Success"]
[White "5b) Stack Your Pieces Before Opening the File"]
[Black "5b) Example 1"]
