{ The [e4]-[d5] vs [e5]-[d6] structure is typical for KID or Ruy López type of position. Here, the kingside is completely shut down, so we should focus on the queenside. There is tension between the [a4] and [b5]-pawns. This should come to our mind to be patient and stack. } 
1.Ra3 $1 {[%cal Ra4b5]} {[%csl Ga4]} {[%csl Rb5]} { Preparing to stack on the a-file. } ( { The hasty ✕ } 1.axb5?! axb5 2.Ra2 {(now White can't play [Ra3] would allow)} 2...Nb6! 3.Bxb6 Qxb6 4.Rca1 Qb7! { , and White can hardly make progress on the open file. } ) Nb6  
2.Bxb6  Qxb6  
3.Rca1 $1 {[%cal Gc2a2]} { White will win the fight on the a-file and get an advantage. }  *

