{ An Indian Defense resembling position, where White has managed to play [b2]-[b4] under good conditions. How to proceed? } 
1.bxc5 $1 { It's best to open up the b-file immediately for specific reasons. } ( { ✓ } 1.Na4 { looks more sophisticated, but actually after } 1...Nd7 2.bxc5 bxc5 { . There is no [b6]-square left, and [Bd8] is possible next. In case of } 3.Nb6 Rb8! { , Black fights back. } ) ( { It is also too slow to start with ✓ } 1.Rb3 { . As Black can organize their defensive setup on the queenside: } 1...Nd7 2.Rcb1 Bd8! 3.bxc5 bxc5 4.Bc2 Bc7 { , and the two bishops control the entrance squares – an important defensive concept to know. } ) bxc5  
2.Rb6 $1 {[%cal Gb6d6]} { Preventing ...[Bd8]. } Nd7  
