{ The outpost, also known as a stronghold along the open file, should be a prime target for our pieces whenever one exists. Knights are the most eager to claim these strongholds, and we know that even investing extra time to reach them – by rerouting – can be highly rewarding. However, knights aren’t the only pieces that should aim for strongholds. We should develop the instinct not to exchange rooks too quickly along the open file but to fight for it by considering patient, strategic moves along the file – especially on key squares like strongholds. As we will see, occupying the stronghold first can provide significant advantages. That's why we need to act as quickly as possible when the opportunity arises to create an outpost. } 
1.--   *

[Event "Healthy Opening Habits for Middlegame Success"]
