{ This kind of position could arise from some Nimzo-Indian variations, where White gets the [c3]-[c4] double pawns. The [c4]-pawn is under attack. How can we defend it? } 
1.Nf1 $1 {[%cal Gf1e3]} {[%cal Ge3d5]} {[%csl Bd5]} { The knight is headed towards [d5]. } ( { I hope the candidate move ❌ } 1.Rd5?! { comes naturally to you at this point, although it's too much here. After } 1...Bxd5 2.cxd5 Ne7 { , Black has the ...[Nc8]-...[Nd6] plan, and even if White clearly has some compensation, it's most likely not enough for the exchange. } ) Bxc4  
