{ This underrated technique may seem unnatural at first, but fighting for open files involves using squares along files that don't seem stable at first glance. We are often taught to invade with heavy pieces to target weaknesses in the enemy camp, but this isn’t always feasible. Interposing a light piece can strengthen our grip on the open file before committing to an invasion. However, even a light piece will restrict key squares near the open file, influencing the position more than it seems at first sight. In some cases, these pieces can even become surprisingly powerful weapons. } 
1.--   *

