1.Bxd5 $3 { An unusual decision at first glance, but after } ( { In the game Garry played ✓ } 1.Rfc1 { and after } 1...Bh6! { , Kramnik was in good shape. } ) Rxd5  ( { ✅ } 1...exd5 2.Nb6 { is objectively better for Black, but White's knights are dominating. } ) 
2.b4  { The idea of [Nb6] will grant White full control of the c-file, as the [c8]-key square is now under control, and Black faces difficulties developing their queenside pieces. }  *

