{ A classical Réti Double-Fianchetto position. What is a typical plan here for White? } 
1.Bc3 $1 {[%cal Gb2c3]} {[%cal Gc2b2]} {[%cal Gb3b4]} { This has a double idea: build the [Bc3]-[Qb2] battery, and prepare the [b3]-[b4] expansion. White has to be careful about not getting pulled back because of the [e6]-[e5] and [d5]-[d4] expansion. } ( { ✓ } 1.Qc3?! Qb6 { , and it's hard for White to progress on the queenside. } )  *

