{ A position from the Maróczy bind, coming from the Paulsen Opening. Recently, Black has been struggling with the lines connected to the classical ...[d6]-...[Nbd7] plan, but the ...[Nc6] and ...[Nxd4] provided some extra ideas. On the last move, White recaptured with the bishop on [d4]. How should Black proceed? } Bd6 $1 { The battery is quite powerful on the [h2]-[b8] diagonal. In the case of [g2]-[g3], Black can try to put more pressure by pushing ...[h7]-[h5]. }  *

