{ A typical Hedgehog-Maróczy position. What kind of battery should Black build and why? } Bd8 $5 {[%cal Bd8c7]} {[%cal Gb8h2]} {[%cal Gd6d5]} {[%cal Bc7h2]} {[%csl Rh2]} { Preparing ...[Bc7] is a typical maneuver, targeting the weakened [h2]-[b8] diagonal. Black is also getting ready for the thematic ...[d6]-[d5] at the right moment. } ( { ✓ } 1...Qa8?! { isn't really doing much, as White is very solid along the [g2]-[a8] diagonal. } ) ( { ✓ } 1...h5 { is the classic approach, launching the h-pawn along the kingside flank. I like the nickname 'Roberto Carlos' for this pawn! } ) { Note from Chessable: Roberto Carlos born in 1973 is a legendary footballer who played for Real Madrid and the Brazilian national team. He was a gifted free-kick taker and, hence the author's reference, an attacking left-back. }  *

