{ An advanced position from a Carlsbad pawn structure, where Black exchanged the strong White's knight on [e5] and just played ...[f6] to eliminate the brand new [e5]-pawn. } 
1.Bc2 $1 { White reverses the order along the [b1]-[h7] diagonal, and suddenly with the queen behind, the threats are very serious. } fxe5  ( { ✅ } 1...Bd7 { is objectively better, but White is still much better after the precise } 2.exf6! Rxf6 3.Rxf6! Qxf6 4.Rf1 { , followed by [Qd3]. } ) 
2.Rxf8+ $1 { Eliminating the rook and bringing the other rook in with a tempo. } Qxf8  
3.Rf1 $1 Qe7  
4.dxe5 $1 {[%cal Gd2d3]} { Qd3 will be fatal. }  *

