1.O-O $1 { Clearly the most desired move to make, but it is important that White has a strong response after ...[c5]-[c4]. } c4  { Not the only move, but a critical one. } 
2.Re1+ $1 { Without this move, White would have no advantage aspiration whatsoever. } ( 2.Be2 Bd6 { and White would have to lose a couple of important tempi. } ) Be7  { Too bad Black has to develop the bishop on this more passive square, compared to [d6]. } 
3.Bf1  {[%cal Gb2b3]} { White is perfectly coordinated, preparing [b2]-[b3]. }  *

