{ A typical position from the Caro-Kann Defense: Tartakower Variation. The next move from Black should come naturally, having in mind the response against White's potential [c4]-[c5]. } Rc8 $1 {[%cal Gd6b8]} { White doesn't necessarily want to play [c4]-[c5], but it is in Black's interest to have the Q+A battery available along the [b8]-[h2] diagonal. } 
2.Nc3  Bb8 $1 {[%cal Gd8d6]} {[%cal Gb7b5]} {[%cal Bc8c2]} {[%csl Rc2]} { The rook is in play before playing this preparatory move. Besides having the possibility of playing a move like ...[Qd6] or ...[Qc7], Black also has the ...[b7]-[b5]!? break option. }  *

