[FEN "r1bq1rk1/ppp1npbp/3p1np1/3Pp3/2P1P3/2N2N2/PP2BPPP/R1BQ1RK1 w - - 0 1"]

{ In the initial position of the Mar del Plata Variation of King's Indian, both sides have plans to reposition their knights behind their pawn chain. } 
1.Ne1 $5 {[%cal Ge1d3]} {[%cal Gf2f3]} { The idea is to bring the knight to a square like [d3], and at the same time protect the pawn chain with an eventual [f2]-[f3]. } Nd7  {[%cal Rf7f5]} { Black's main counterplay is clearly on the kingside and ...[f7]-[f5] should be played in the next moves, so ...[Nf6]-...[Nd7] or ...[Nf6]-...[Ne8] are typical moves here. }  *

[Event "Healthy Opening Habits for Middlegame Success"]
