[Black "6c) Example 3"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "r1b2rk1/ppp2pp1/2n2q1p/3p4/1b1P4/2NBPN2/PP3PPP/R2Q1RK1 b - - 0 1"]

{ Coming from a Ragozin Variation, sometimes the knight is forced to get to [c6], as the [b4]-bishop has to be defended. Sometimes people simply forget that the knight isn't supposed to be developed in front of central pawns. } Ne7  {[%cal Gc7c6]} {[%cal Ge7f5]} {[%cal Ge7g6]} {[%csl Bb7]} {[%csl Bc6]} {[%csl Bd5]} { Once this move is played, things start looking brighter. The move ...[c7]-[c6] is on agenda, creating the strong [b7]-[c6]-[d5] chain, and Black can start repositioning their minor pieces. }  *

