[FEN "r1bq1rk1/1pp2pbp/n2p1np1/p2Pp3/2P1P3/2N1BN2/PP2BPPP/R2QK2R w KQ - 0 1"]

{ Can you find a perfect example of achieving harmony? } 
1.Nd2 $1 {[%cal Gg2g4]} {[%cal Gh2h4]} { An aesthetically pleasant move to play. The knight is repositioned from being located in front of the f-pawn. } { The advantages are multiple: 🔹no more ...[Ng4] ideas; 🔹the [e3]-bishop is not blocked on [c1]*; and, 🔹White is ready to take space with [g4] and [h4]. ∗ If White plays the move [Nf3]-[d2] with the bishop still on [c1], the [d2]-knight would 'block' the [c1]-bishop, as the purpose of [Nf3]-[d2] is to be able to play [g2]-[g4] later on. }  *

