{ This is a position from the Berlin Defense. White has played the slow 4.d3 and Black successfully played ...d7-d5, taking space in the center. What next? } Nb8 $1 {[%cal Gb8d7]} {[%cal Gc7c6]} {[%csl Rc6]} { Apparently, getting the [b8]-knight in shape is a priority here, too. Once the knight will be on [d7], it can later be moved to [f8] after [Re8] or [Rd8]. } ( { ✅ The repositioning move } 1...Nd8 { with the idea of ...[Ne6] is also perfectly playable. } )  *

[Event "Healthy Opening Habits for Middlegame Success"]
[White "6c) Reposition Your Knight Behind the Pawns"]
