{ This is a game of mine, where I was Black. It seems like Black has developed their pieces harmoniously, placing the rooks on the central squares. However, with their next move, White showed me that I was far from being right, despite it not being the top move. This was one of the reasons I started to play the English with White! How would you play? } 
1.Nh4 $1 { The point of this move is that it still kind of stops ...[d6]-[d5] although it was hard to play anyway, and the knight on [h4] is more active. Black is yet again in half zugzwang, and ...[g7]-[g5] would be a huge weakening move. } ( { In the game, White played the elegant ✓ } 1.Ng1!? { , preparing [Nge2]. Black is suddenly out of good moves with all the pieces on the board! I felt completely outplayed. } ) ( { ✓ } 1.Ne1 { is also possible, preparing [Nc2]. However, I feel that [Nge2] is more harmonious. } )  *

[Event "Healthy Opening Habits for Middlegame Success"]
