{ A typical slow Catalan scenario. There are little to no pawn breaks in this position. How can White improve their position? } 
1.Kg2 $1 {[%cal Gg1g2]} {[%cal Gh1h3]} {[%cal Gh3f3]} {[%cal Gf3f1]} {[%cal Gf1h1]} { This move improves White's king position. Although it's not a major improvement, we can see that Black doesn't have a light-squared bishop. Therefore, White's king is perfectly safe. [h2]-[h4] is another move on White's agenda. } ( { ✓ } 1.Ne5!? { stops [g6], but puts White under potential ...[c6]-[c5]. } ) ( { I am not sure the move ✓ } 1.e4 { actually helps White, as the pawn is positioned on the same color of White's bishop. Besides, Black can take some space by playing } 1...g6 { , followed by ...[Kg7] next. } )  *

