{ A position from the critical Bayonet Attack variation in the KID already old-fashioned 7...Nc6 line. } 
1.a4 $1 {[%cal Gf3d2]} {[%cal Gd2b3]} {[%cal Bc5a5]} {[%cal Ba5a1]} {[%cal Ba1c1]} {[%cal Bc1c5]} {[%cal Ba1a5]} {[%cal Ba5c5]} {[%cal Bc5c1]} {[%cal Bc1a1]} { White is ready to conquer more squares on the queenside. Next will be [Nd2]-[Nb3] and [a5]. The [a1]-[a5]-[c5]-[c1] rectangle will now be under White's control. } ( { ✓ } 1.Bd2?! { is quite unambitious, as the bishop can be eventually developed to a more active square, such as [e3]. } )  *

