{ In my game against Fabiano Caruana, White played a typical idea here. Some time ago, something similar would be called a weakening operation, but in reality it's filling empty space. } 
1.g4 $5 Nhf6  
2.h3  {[%cal Gd2f4]} {[%cal Gh4f4]} {[%cal Gf4f2]} {[%cal Gf2h2]} {[%cal Gh2h4]} ( 2. h3 { It's important that Black can't really challenge White's h3-g4 chain, as after } 2...h5 { , White would answer with 3.g5 } { , gaining even more space. } ) ( 2. h3 { It's important to point out that } 2...Ne4 { is not available for Black, while } {2...Ne5 runs into 3.Nxe5 Rxe5 4.Bf4! or even 4.e4 and 4.f4 . } )  *

