{ In this Giuoco Piano with ...[a7]-[a6] starting position, Black has different plans, but generally, the move ...[a7]-[a6] is followed by a prophylactic move. } Ba7 $5 {[%cal Rd3d4]} { This move allows Black to forget about the dangers of [d3]-[d4]. From [a7] the bishop keeps applying pressure on the [a7]-[g1] diagonal. } ( { Moreover, on a7, it remains safe: if } 1...Bb6 (, White's knight could chase it away with 2.Nc4 , and Black lose a tempo.) )  *

