{ The London System has gained extremely popularity thanks to Magnus Carlsen. Nowadays, it's a popular weapon, although I am not a huge fan of it. Here, White chose to play a relatively quiet version of it. What is useful to do here for White? } 
1.Bh2 $1 {[%csl Gh2]} { This is a generally healthy move to make. White avoids any ...[e7]-[e5] ideas that come with a tempo, and ...[Nfd5] moves. Moreover, the bishop from [h2] once again keeps doing its job, putting pressure on the [h2]-[b8] diagonal. The only potential downside is that the first rank checkmate is now possible, if Black lands a rook there. }  *

