{ A position from the Carlsbad pawn structure, where Black played [c7]-[c5] after White's [f2]-[f3]. Which bishop to reposition and where? } 
1.Bc2 $1 { A strong preparatory move, defending [d4] and intending both [dxc5] followed by [Nd4] and the immediate [Nf4]. } ( { ✅ } 1.Rc1 { is a sound move, although allowing [cxd4]. } 1...cxd4 2.exd4 { . White is probably slightly better, but not as much as after 1.Bc2. } {(( 2.Nxd4 is followed by 2...Nxd4 3.exd4 Qb6! with counterplay. ))} ) cxd4  {✅1...Rc8 2.dxc5! Bxc5 3.Nd4 . A typical position in this opening, where Black may be left with unpromising light pieces on the kingside. } 
2.Nxd4 $1 Nxd4  
3.exd4  { White will be able to play [Bb3] later, as there is no ...[Na5]. }  *

