{ In the mainline of the Scotch with 4...Nf6, White just played 8.h4 . It has recently become more popular than the old 8.c4 . Black has several ways to proceed here, but pushing the isolated pawn can have several ideas. } a5 $5 {[%cal Gc8a6]} { The main point of ...[a7]-[a5] is to prepare ...[Ba6], followed by ...[O-O-O]. Eventually, Black will organize counterplay in the center. By playing ...[a7]-[a5] and ...[Ba6], Black is trying to prevent White from developing with harmony. }  *

