1.a4 $5 {[%cal Ga4a5]} { This pawn threatens to be annoying by being pushed forward to [a5]. If Black stops it by playing ...[a7]-[a5] themselves, then after [Rb1], White will have more pressure along the b-file. } ( { ✓ } 1.Nd2 { is also possible as a regrouping move. However, Black is generally happier to face a slower game from White. } )  *

