{ A position in the Jobava London with ...[g6]. Black decided to play ...[Bg4] and ...[Bxf3], eliminating the potentially annoying knight jumping to [e5]. What to do now with the h-pawn? Is it worth advancing it? } 
1.e4 $1 { This is connected to the chapter where we provide space for our bishops. White takes space in the center and prepares [Be3] in case of ...[Nh5]. } ( { ✕ } 1.h4?! { . There is no attack here, so [h4] is just a waste of time. Furthermore, after } 1...Nh5! 2.Bh2 Nd7 { , White will be unable to play [e3]-[e4], as their center might be vulnerable. ...[e7]-[e5] is also a possibility for Black. } ) Nh5  
2.Be3 $1 { White has a better control in the center. In case Black decides to castle short, White will have both [Ne2]-[Ng3] and [Bh3]-[Bg4] plans to remove the [h5]-knight. }  *

