{ A famous theoretical position, where White decided to play [Bg5]. Black's long-term strategy is to contest the center by pushing ...[c7]-[c5] so that the central files will be opened. That's why the move ...[h7]-[h6] is useful, as when Black is castled, there will be space for the king. } h6 $1 { White has a couple of options, although the move [Bh4] is the most common reply. }  *

[Event "Healthy Opening Habits for Middlegame Success"]
