{ This starting position is a tabia in the Caro-Kann: 3.Nc3 Variation. Think about it, what are the pluses and minuses of pushing [h4]-[h5] here? } 
1.Bd3 $1 { Nowadays, playing without [h4]-[h5] is considered to be more promising for White. Leaving the pawn on [h4] gives Whites two extra possibilities: the first is removing the [g3]-knight and pushing [g4]-[g5], in case White castles short. The second is the possibility of jumping with the knight on [h5] later on. } ( { ✅ } 1.h5 Bh7 2.Bd3 {(has been the main line for many years. The main plus of the move [h5] is that the [g7]- and [h6]-pawns are fixed, and in a hypothetical endgame, the h-pawn might be closer to promotion. However, plenty of play exists before the endgame, and the [h5]-pawn might be weak in some lines. Also, Black can now castle short this is considered to be best from a theoretical point of view, as [g4]-[g5] is less powerful.)} )  *

