1.b5 $1 {[%cal Gb2a3]} {[%cal Gf1c1]} {[%cal Gc1c7]} {[%csl Bb5]} {[%csl Rb6]} {[%csl Rc7]} {[%csl Rd5]} { By fixing the [d5]-pawn, this becomes a long-term target. If Black will try to play ...[c7]-[c6] at some point, after capturing en passant, the [d5]-pawn will remain weak. Although, at the moment, White doesn't have many attackers, the [d5]-pawn is going to be an issue once White has rerouted their pieces, such as the knight to [c3] and the light-squared bishop to the [h1]-[a8] diagonal. The [c7]-pawn is now backward, and ideas like [Ba3] followed by putting pressure on the c-file are also possible. }  *

