2.Nxb4 $1 { A non-standard recapture, aiming at opening more lines. } ( { ✕ } 2.cxb4 { would be too slow, and Black could continue with } 2...f5! { with attacking possibilities on the kingside. } ) Nxb4  
3.Rxb4  {[%cal Gb4b7]} Bxa2  
4.Rxa2  b6 $6 ( { ✅ } 4...Rxc3 { is objectively better for Black compared to [b6], but White is still better with the rook on the 7th rank after } 5.Rxb7 { . } ) 
5.c4  {[%cal Ga4a5]} {[%csl Ga5]} { Now we see the purpose of leaving the rook on [a1]. The isolated a-pawn can now be pushed forward, opening more lines. }  *

