{ In the Chigorin Ruy López's starting position, White immediately decided to close the center by playing 12.d5. Black's here by far most played move 12...[Bd7] is considered nowadays to be quite a big mistake! Why, and what is the absolute main move here today? } Nc4 $1 { It's important to bring knight back to life. } ( { ✓ } 1...Bd7?! { In case of } 2.b3! 2...Nb7 3.Be3 { the knight would be sad on [b7]. If } 3...c4 4.b4 a5 { , White can just keep things as they are, while dominating the [b7]-knight or even consider blowing up the queenside with [a2]-[a4], exploiting poor coordination of Black's pieces. } ) 
2.b3  Nb6 $1 {[%cal Gc5c4]} {[%cal Ga6a5]} { Black will now be able to advance their pawns, creating potential counterplay on the queenside. } 
3.Be3  c4 $1 {[%cal Ga6a5]} {[%cal Gc8d7]} { Now [b3]-[b4] would be terrible, as the knight from [b6] would get an excellent square on [a4]. }  *

